rComments: She is so sweet, and her classes are interesting!! Very very straightforward material. What she says in class and presents - is on the exams and final! Will definitely take more classes with her, she's awesome!

This was one of the worst classes I've EVER taken in my entire university. She told us what to study before the midterms and every student was ready for it but instead she surprised all of us by telling us we had to read a 30 page text and answer question in less then an hour! One of the worst profs I've ever had. AVOID TAKING HER ONLINE!

By far the best prof I've had. She is so caring about her students, goes above and beyond to make sure they succeed. Her lectures are really interesting She tells you EXACTLY what to study for the exam so no surprises. This is the 3rd class I take with her (GEG3506/GEG3704) and her other classes are no exceptions. Best prof for a good elective!!

Very passionate professor who cares about her students. Tests are fair; she narrows down the notes specifically to the exam, so if you study what she says, there is no reason to do bad in this course. Highly recommend taking any course with this prof!

Une classe très intéressante donnée par une prof très passionnée de ce qu'elle enseigne. Les exigences pour les examens et le travail d'équipe sont très claires. Il est claire qu'elle veut la réussite de tous ces étudiants. Je recommande cette prof pour tous le monde, la meilleure!!!

Always 5-15 minutes late to class, material isn't hard but you are not encouraged to think for yourself, only regurgitate powerpoints. She is fairly lazy, I had some questions for her and she made me feel like she didnt want to be there.

Très bonne prof! Elle est très précise sur ce qu'elle veut à l'examen donc il est important d'assister aux classes pour savoir quoi étudier. Si l'étude est fait proprement, c'est très facile de bien réussir son cours.

Elle un prof génial! Avant chaque mi-terme elle dit le powerpoints qu'il faut apprendre, pour que rien sur les tests soient une surprise. Ceci dit, les test sont asssez facile, puisqu'il faut juste récrire les mots clefs qui étaient sur le powerpoints qu'elle a indiquer. Le tests/examen final sont non-cumulatif. Overall 19/10, would take again.
Super cool prof teaching and even cooler class. I'm a science student that took this as an elective and LOVED it. Easy and interesting material that was very well explained for tests.

Kenza est une bonne professeure de géographie humaine. Ses cours sont intéressant, mais elle n'intéragit pas avec ses étudiants en cours (style conférencière). Les examens sont assez facile, mais c'est du par coeur. Avant l'examen elle dit exactement ce qu'il faut "comprendre", "retenir" et "connitre". Pour ce cours, il y a 2 examens de 45%

Excellente prof et matière très intéressante. Apprends sur la formation et les caractéristiques des villes de chaque continent. Présence  10%, exam mi-session  30%, Projet de groupe (ou individuel) sur une ville d'Amérique latine  30% et examen final  30%. Un bon cours au choix agréable.

She's a really good at communicating information, I would take her again. Her exams are really easy, but you still need to study the material in order to do well. The TA's correction is really picky when it comes to the big essay worth 30% of your grade.

Kenza's GEG3707 is a fascinating course, interesting slides with many pictures and examples. Highly recommend to all students, papers can be submitted in either language. Such a nice prof, remembers her students and is always willing to help with a smile! Interesting projects with clear grading criteria. Encourages group work but is not enforced.

The nicest most amazing teacher, always happily accepts a line of students after class who have questions. Allows papers to be submitted in French or English. Midterm and final criteria is given slide by slide from the lectures, super clear expectations. Very interesting course content, Kenza knows her material and what to teach. My favourite prof!

Meilleure professeure! Explique extrêmement bien et connais très bien sa matière. Les examens sont équitables, si tu étudies tu vas bien faire. La professeure est très gentille et aimable. Je vous conseille de prendre ce cours avec kenza!

Définitivement, LA meilleure prof que j'ai eu à l'univesité. Elle est toujours la pour ses élèves, très sympatique et appochable. Les classes sont très intéressantes et captivant. JE la recommande fortement!!!!

As a French immersion student I had no problem understanding lectures. I chose to write my projecttests in French, but the option is available for English. Straightforward lectures of essential knowledge which Kenza describes very well.  Simply wonderful teacher, very nice, and always available to talk. Recommend highly, my absolute favourite!

So easy. She details every piece of information that will be on the exams. The exams are simple knowledge questions and there isn't any thinking involved. If you miss a class you lose 1%, unless you have a good reason, but she'll only excuse you three times no matter what. Incredibly interesting but all fact based,  no deep thinking involved.
She is one of the best professors at UOttawa! Her lectures are clear and her exams are to the point! She is so fair and nice, and I learned a lot from her course!
Très bonne enseignante, assitez en classe
Simplement LA meilleur. Elle est claire et directe c'est classe passe très vite avec la matière pertinente qu'elle enseigne et elle fais souvent cadeau d'examen facile de mi-session et examen finale
cours et professeur très intéressant!
The easiest course of my life, gives ridiculously high notes.
Very interesting course
Huge class from different areas.  A little challenging for group oral presentations due to the size of the groups.
If you went to class, you will ace the tests.
Very interesting course.  If you go to class you will know exactly what to do for group presentations.
Awesome prof!Very interesting course.

Excellente prof, ecoutez en classe et allez en classe. Le cours avant l'examen elle dit sur quelles diapos il faut se concentrer, ca il y aura des questions sur ces diapos a l'examen. Les examens ont une dizaine de questions TRES faciles si vous etudiez, le travail a rendre est simple aussi, il faut juste s'y mettre. Un A+ tres facile si on s'y met

this professor makes every and each class very interesting and attractive + her sens of humor brings another taste to the subject. Her international profile helps her analyzing each subject under different angles. I strongly recommend to U.Ottawa students looking for a GEO class to take a class offered by KEnza. She is amazing.
definitely one of the best teachers I have ever had in my 4 years at the university of Ottawa. she makes the subject very interesting and the clarity of her speech is very helpful.

C'est un Prof. passionnée par la géographie urbaine et transmet bien sa passion. On sent qu'elle prépare ces cours avant de venir les exposer. Elle a du temps pour ces étudiants même en dehors des cours, son soutien pédagogique est manifeste. J'ai eu le plaisir de prendre un cours avec elle, j'ai hâte de refaire cette expérience enrichissante.

I had this teacher for 2 courses and I would take so many more. She is so interesting and very passionate about what she is teaching. She is an incredible professor who cares about her students' success. She got me even more hooked to geography, making me want to minor in it. I overall really enjoyed her interacting lectures with ppts and videos.

C'est une excellente prof qui prend véritablement le temps pour ces étudiants et qui disponible en dehors des cours. Elle s'investit beaucoup dans la préparation de ces cours offre un enseignement stimulant et enrichissant.

Lors de mon bac, j'ai eu la chance de prendre plusieurs cours donnés par Kenza Benali. La matière vue en classe est toujours très intéressante. À l'aide de vidéo, de conférenciers et de travaux pratiques, cette prof transmet   véritablement sa passion pour la géographie urbaine.

This is the second course I take with her. She is dynamic and enthusiastic! Very approachable and available.Her lessons are clear and well planned out, her teaching contains a variety of approaches making it stimulating rather than dry. Anyone interested in Urban Geography from a national and internationa perspective must take her class! loved it!
good

Kenza is a wonderful professor! Very welcoming! It is obvious that her passion lies in her research and not necessarily teaching. Either way this is the third class that I have taken with her, she offers an alternative way of learning (guest speakers, group projects, movies etc.) However, it is always my `bird course` for the semester.
Moi, j'ai adoré son cours sur les Villes orientales. La prof est passionnée par sa matière et le voyage organisé pour la Tunisie a été une expérience géniale.

Decent prof. Definitely not my favorite, but she speaks clearly and is easy to understand. Knows her subject material (in this case: the geography of arab countries). not overly interesting, and is a bit 'lazy' (doesn't always lecture/do anything, assignments that are really easy to mark, lots of semi-useless videos). Overall, I give her a B-

Lazy prof - She gave 2, maybe 3 lectures the entire semestre, the rest were guest lecturers and class presentations. She's a pretty dull lecturer anyways though. Her exams were laughable though: ALL short answers that were insultingly simplistic for a uni course.
